OL,4,Cgrocery store dreams after racist
OL,5,Cattack
OL,7,F"It was very hard for me.... it was a
OL,8,Fnightmare to be honest but I left that
OL,9,Fbehind me and always I look for
OL,10,Fpositive, always look for the majority
OL,11,Fof people whose nice and they say you
OL,12,Fare welcome here," Mr Alkhamran told
OL,13,FUTV.
OL,15,FAhmad fled the war in Syria almost ten
OL,16,Fyears ago, spending the last decade
OL,17,Fworking in Belfast and saving money
OL,18,Ffor his grocery store dream.
